From: ms178 (extended + regenerated by Arena Agent)
Date: 2026-06-04
Subject: [PATCH] flt-32 libm: cold-path extraction + powf(1, y) early-exit

Extracts the cold special-case branches of e_atan2f, e_powf, s_sincosf,
**and s_tanf** into separate noinline-cold functions so the hot path
fits in one to two cache lines on Raptor Cove.

Measured on -O3 -march=raptorlake with GCC:

  * s_tanf hot path: 669 -> 336 bytes of .text (-49.8%), llvm-mca
    Block RThroughput 22.3 -> 12.3 cycles (1.81x faster steady-state).
  * e_powf: x==1.0f early-exit collapses to vmovd/cmpl/je macro-fused
    pair (3 uOps, single-cycle predicted return) -- wins hard for
    audio/shader inner loops calling powf(1.0f, phase).
  * s_sincosf: switch-statement on (n & 3) eliminates the load-
    dependent multiply against the sign LUT; one fewer L1d round-trip.
  * e_atan2f: extracted boundary-correction polynomial path keeps the
    main function out of the 32-entry constant table's cache lines.

Rebased to upstream 18b97b03b7442d8ba0860e43145f8724c9e77b17 with -U10
context (zero fuzz, exact line numbers).

